    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To make matters worse, if you remove the \"<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>κ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\kappa</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord mathit\">κ</span></span></span></span>-\" part of the terminology, then they become new terms with meanings which relate to the original ones in different ways. A filtered category is one which is <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℵ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\aleph_0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.84444em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">ℵ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathrm mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>-filtered, but in other places we insert \"finitely\" in place of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℵ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\aleph_0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.84444em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">ℵ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathrm mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, and \"locally presentable\" means locally <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>κ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\kappa</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord mathit\">κ</span></span></span></span>-presentable for some <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>κ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\kappa</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord mathit\">κ</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 133613343,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1536505273
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Things I thought about: something like <code>filtered_wrt κ</code> or <code>filtered_rel κ</code> for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>κ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\kappa</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord mathit\">κ</span></span></span></span>-filtered, but it's not really standard terminology.</p>",
        "id": 133613436,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1536505373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's probably some more familiar examples as well, like being a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord mathit\">p</span></span></span></span>-group.</p>",
        "id": 133613472,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1536505441
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How would you want to write that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord mathit\">G</span></span></span></span> is a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord mathit\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span></span></span></span>-group, or a 2-group?</p>",
        "id": 133613548,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1536505546
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We currently have <code>zmodp</code> (contrast <code>zmod</code>) and <code>padic_*</code>, but the use of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord mathit\">p</span></span></span></span> may be a special case as far as naming goes.</p>",
        "id": 133613887,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryan Gin-ge Chen",
        "timestamp": 1536505949
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess the names with <code>kappa</code> (or maybe <code>κ</code>) in the middle aren't so bad.</p>",
        "id": 133614434,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1536506770
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm also tempted by</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"kn\">notation</span> <span class=\"n\">κ</span> <span class=\"bp\">`-</span><span class=\"n\">filtered</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">max</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">kappa_filtered</span> <span class=\"n\">κ</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>but I don't know whether that is mathlib-approved</p>",
        "id": 133614776,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1536507214
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We also have that kind of problem in symplectic topology. We things called J-holomorphic curves, or ξ-convex surfaces, even when we don't specify an almost complex structure J or a contact structure ξ</p>",
        "id": 133620266,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
